@startuml
title Eclipse SDV E2E Demo Blueprint - Full Device and Component Architecture
left to right direction
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam componentStyle rectangle

actor "Driver" as Driver
actor "Fleet Operator" as Operator
cloud "Vehicle LAN\n(Wi-Fi / Ethernet)" as VehicleLAN
cloud "CAN Bus\n500 kbit/s" as CANBus
cloud "Backend Network\n(fms-backend)" as BackendNet

node "Driver Input ECU - Joystick\n(Arduino Uno R4 WiFi)" as ECU_JOYSTICK {
  component "Joystick Sensor\n(analog + button)" as JOY_SENSOR
  component "WiFiS3" as JOY_WIFI
  component "MQTT Publisher\nTopic: InVehicleTopics" as JOY_MQTT
}

node "Driver Input ECU - Door\n(Arduino + RC522 RFID)" as ECU_DOOR {
  component "RC522 RFID Reader" as DOOR_SENSOR
  component "WiFiS3" as DOOR_WIFI
  component "MQTT Publisher\nVehicle.Driver.Identifier.Subject" as DOOR_MQTT
}

node "ThreadX MCU Device 1\n(MXChip AZ3166, MQTT -> SOME/IP Gateway)" as ECU_THREADX_1 {
  component "NetX Duo Network Stack" as TX1_NET
  component "MQTT Subscriber\nTopics: DirectionIndication, Brake" as TX1_MQTT
  component "Buttons A/B Input" as TX1_BTN
  component "SOME/IP Publisher\n(Wi-Fi UDP notification)" as TX1_SOMEIP_TX
  component "SOME/IP Subscriber\n(Wi-Fi UDP notification)" as TX1_SOMEIP_RX
  component "Remote Button State Handler" as TX1_APP
}

node "ThreadX MCU Device 2\n(MXChip AZ3166, SOME/IP Peer)" as ECU_THREADX_2 {
  component "NetX Duo Network Stack" as TX2_NET
  component "Buttons A/B Input" as TX2_BTN
  component "SOME/IP Publisher\n(Wi-Fi UDP notification)" as TX2_SOMEIP_TX
  component "SOME/IP Subscriber\n(Wi-Fi UDP notification)" as TX2_SOMEIP_RX
  component "Remote State Handler\n(LED/OLED/UI update)" as TX2_APP
}

node "MCU1 LED Control ECU\n(Arduino Uno + MCP2515)" as ECU_LED {
  component "CAN Interface\n(MCP2515 @ 500 kbit/s)" as LED_CAN
  component "Blinker/Brake Logic" as LED_LOGIC
  component "WS2812 8-LED Strip" as LED_STRIP
}

node "Raspberry Pi 5 - Unified Vehicle + Fleet Host" as PI5 {
  component "Eclipse Ankaios\n(agent_B + Podman)" as ANKAIOS
  frame "Signal Workloads (Podman)" as PI5_WORKLOADS {
    component "Mosquitto Broker\n:1883" as MOSQ
    component "grpc-mqtt-bridge" as BRIDGE
    component "Kuksa Databroker\n:55555" as KDB_VEHICLE
    component "Kuksa CAN Provider\n(dbc2val + val2dbc)" as CAN_PROVIDER
  }
  component "SocketCAN\ncan0" as SOCKETCAN
  artifact "VSS/CAN Mapping\n(motorbike-blinker-vss.json + .dbc)" as VSS_CAN_MAP
  frame "Fleet Management + Analytics (Docker Compose)" as FMS_STACK {
    component "fms-forwarder" as FMS_FORWARDER
    component "fms-consumer" as FMS_CONSUMER
    component "fms-zenoh-router" as FMS_ZENOH
    component "fms-server\nHTTP rFMS API :8081" as FMS_SERVER
    component "fleet-analysis-backend\nJakarta EE API :8082" as ANALYSIS_API
    database "InfluxDB 2.7" as INFLUX
    component "Grafana" as GRAFANA
    component "csv-provider\n(simulation source, optional)" as CSV_PROVIDER
    component "Kuksa Databroker\n(fleet stack variant)" as KDB_FLEET
  }
  component "HCP Control Apps\n(optional placeholder)" as HCP
}

node "Raspberry Pi 4 - Placeholder" as PI4 {
  component "Future split deployment target\n(optional)" as PI4_PLACEHOLDER
}

Driver --> JOY_SENSOR : joystick movement / press
Driver --> DOOR_SENSOR : RFID card tap

JOY_SENSOR --> JOY_MQTT
DOOR_SENSOR --> DOOR_MQTT

JOY_MQTT --> VehicleLAN : MQTT JSON
DOOR_MQTT --> VehicleLAN : MQTT JSON

VehicleLAN --> MOSQ : MQTT publish/subscribe
MOSQ --> BRIDGE : subscribed topic\nInVehicleTopics
BRIDGE --> KDB_VEHICLE : gRPC Val/Set updates
MOSQ --> TX1_MQTT : subscribe\nDirectionIndication, Brake
TX1_MQTT --> TX1_SOMEIP_TX : map MQTT payload to SOME/IP event
TX1_BTN --> TX1_SOMEIP_TX : provide Button A/B pressed state
TX1_SOMEIP_TX --> VehicleLAN : SOME/IP over Wi-Fi (UDP)
VehicleLAN --> TX2_SOMEIP_RX : SOME/IP event delivery
TX2_SOMEIP_RX --> TX2_APP : apply remote direction/brake/button state
TX2_BTN --> TX2_SOMEIP_TX : provide Button A/B pressed state
TX2_SOMEIP_TX --> VehicleLAN : SOME/IP over Wi-Fi (UDP)
VehicleLAN --> TX1_SOMEIP_RX : SOME/IP event delivery
TX1_SOMEIP_RX --> TX1_APP : apply remote Button A/B state

KDB_VEHICLE --> CAN_PROVIDER : target value subscription\n(val2dbc)
CAN_PROVIDER --> KDB_VEHICLE : current value updates\n(dbc2val)
CAN_PROVIDER --> SOCKETCAN
SOCKETCAN --> CANBus : CAN ID 0x120 command\nBlinkerCommand
CANBus --> SOCKETCAN : CAN ID 0x121 status\nBlinkerStatus

LED_CAN --> CANBus
LED_CAN --> LED_LOGIC
LED_LOGIC --> LED_STRIP

HCP --> VehicleLAN : control path
HCP --> KDB_VEHICLE : gRPC set/get (optional supervisory)

KDB_VEHICLE --> FMS_FORWARDER : read/subscribe VSS/FMS signals
CSV_PROVIDER --> KDB_FLEET : optional simulated vehicle data
KDB_FLEET --> FMS_FORWARDER : alternative data source
KDB_VEHICLE .. KDB_FLEET : deployment variant\n(shared or separate Databroker)

FMS_FORWARDER --> FMS_ZENOH : uProtocol notifications
FMS_ZENOH --> FMS_CONSUMER : Zenoh transport
FMS_CONSUMER --> INFLUX : write telemetry
FMS_SERVER --> INFLUX : query telemetry
ANALYSIS_API --> INFLUX : read/write derived stats
GRAFANA --> INFLUX : dashboard queries

Operator --> GRAFANA : dashboard access :3000
Operator --> FMS_SERVER : rFMS API calls :8081
Operator --> ANALYSIS_API : fleet-analysis API :8082

note bottom of PI5
Signal mapping implemented in:
- docs/vss-can-signals.md
- devices/raspberry-pi5/ankaios/*.yaml
- devices/raspberry-pi5/ankaios/*.dbc
Fleet stack service definitions:
- external/fleet-management/fms-blueprint-compose.yaml
- external/fleet-management/fms-blueprint-compose-zenoh.yaml
end note

note bottom of PI4
Current implementation runs fleet + signal workloads on Raspberry Pi 5.
Raspberry Pi 4 is kept as a placeholder for future split deployment.
end note

@enduml
